  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Using a sharp knife, score the <strong>duck skin</strong> on a diagonal, being careful not to cut through to the meat</p>\n<p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then add the <strong>scored duck</strong>, skin-side down, to a cold, dry pan over a low-medium heat</p>\n<p>Cook for 10-15 min, skin-side down only, or until the skin is golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/asian-duck-breast-salad-with-hoisin-dressing/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop ﬁnely</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/asian-duck-breast-salad-with-hoisin-dressing/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once golden, transfer the <strong>duck</strong>, skin-side up, to a baking tray</p>\n<p>Put the tray into the oven for 10-12 min for medium</p>\n<p>Tip: Cook for 3-5 minutes further if you prefer your duck well done</p>\n<p>Once cooked, set the duck aside, cover, and leave to rest for at least 10 min</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/asian-duck-breast-salad-with-hoisin-dressing/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the duck is cooking, boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Combine the <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong> and<strong> soy sauce</strong> with the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p>\n<p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>v</strong><strong>egetable oil</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>hoisin dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/asian-duck-breast-salad-with-hoisin-dressing/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>fine egg noodles</strong> to a large bowl, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir for 10 sec to separate the noodles</p>\n<p>Set aside to soak for 4 min</p>\n<p>Once softened, drain the <strong>noodles</strong> and set aside until serving</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/asian-duck-breast-salad-with-hoisin-dressing/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the noodles are softening, slice the <strong>cucumber</strong> into discs</p>\n<p>Slice each individual <strong>cucumber disc</strong> into <strong>matchsticks </strong></p>\n<p>Trim, then slice the<strong> spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/asian-duck-breast-salad-with-hoisin-dressing/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the duck has rested for 10 min, transfer it to a clean board and slice it finely</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/asian-duck-breast-salad-with-hoisin-dressing/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the<strong> baby leaf salad</strong> between plates, top with the <strong>cucumber matchsticks</strong> and <strong>softened noodles</strong></p>\n<p>Drizzle the <strong>hoisin dressing</strong> all over and top with the <strong>sliced duck breast</strong></p>\n<p>Garnish with the<strong> sliced spring onion</strong>,<strong> black sesame seeds</strong> and remaining<strong> chopped chilli</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
